# previewDocument Function Analysis

The `previewDocument` function uses **backticks (template literals)** throughout. Here's the core structure:

```javascript
function previewDocument(docId) {
  const doc = documentsData.find(d => d.id === docId);
  if (!doc) return;
  const content = doc.document_content || {};
  let html = `<div>...</div>`;

  if (content.form_type === 'I-9') {
    html += `<h2>...</h2>...`;
  } else if (content.form_type === 'W-4') {
    html += `<h2>...</h2>...`;
  }
  // ... more conditions
  html += `<button onclick="closeModal()">Close</button>`;
  document.body.insertAdjacentHTML('beforeend', html);
}
```

**Key finding:** All HTML strings use backticks for template literals with embedded variables like `${escapeHtml(content.employee_name || '')}`. The backticks are used correctly throughout, allowing variable interpolation with `${}` syntax within the string definitions.

